1
00:00:01,061 --> 00:00:02,689
(Conan breathing heavily)

2
00:00:02,772 --> 00:00:04,484
Don't tell me that couple...

3
00:00:05,027 --> 00:00:07,198
were Bourbon and Vermouth...

4
00:00:07,574 --> 00:00:11,039
And what if they overheard
my conversation with Jodie?

5
00:00:12,041 --> 00:00:14,963
I... I've got to find Haibara
and check, fast.

6
00:00:16,007 --> 00:00:19,347
Dammit. Why didn't I
catch on right away?

7
00:00:20,516 --> 00:00:22,687
If they're saying
her husband Touhei...

8
00:00:22,771 --> 00:00:25,401
was also a hostage
in that incident...

9
00:00:25,485 --> 00:00:27,864
then nothing adds up.

10
00:00:28,449 --> 00:00:31,663
Even though they pulled
such a huge blunder...

11
00:00:32,081 --> 00:00:34,252
Huh... a blunder?

12
00:00:36,340 --> 00:00:38,344
Wait, could this be...

13
00:00:38,594 --> 00:00:39,679
a trap?

14
00:00:40,640 --> 00:00:41,850
Huh?

15
00:00:42,227 --> 00:00:45,316
Lately, have you sensed
their presence at all?

16
00:00:45,399 --> 00:00:47,779
Uh... yeah, you know...

17
00:00:47,862 --> 00:00:50,117
You said before you could
smell them, right?

18
00:00:50,451 --> 00:00:54,084
I haven't sensed anything.
I haven't been on my guard.

19
00:00:54,376 --> 00:00:58,050
You told me yourself
they think I'm dead.

20
00:00:58,509 --> 00:01:01,098
Ah... right, right.
Then it's fine.

21
00:01:01,181 --> 00:01:02,600
Wait... what?

22
00:01:02,684 --> 00:01:05,439
Don't tell me they found out
I'm still alive...

23
00:01:05,523 --> 00:01:08,362
It... it's just a check.
Just checking.

24
00:01:08,445 --> 00:01:10,324
Anyway, sorry for calling
this late.

25
00:01:12,704 --> 00:01:15,835
Got to stay calm
and not make a fuss.

26
00:01:19,384 --> 00:01:25,396
♪~

27
00:01:32,368 --> 00:01:36,168
Black shadows and dark gloom,
the light of deduction cuts through.

28
00:01:36,251 --> 00:01:39,716
Ran collapsed during the investigation
with Sera. What on earth happened?

29
00:01:39,966 --> 00:01:41,470
Seeing through the one and only truth.

30
00:01:41,553 --> 00:01:43,390
A child in appearance,
with the mind of an adult.

31
00:01:43,474 --> 00:01:46,313
His name is Detective Conan!

32
00:03:10,504 --> 00:03:16,516
~♪

33
00:03:18,227 --> 00:03:21,627
"The Restroom Where Ran Also Collapsed (Part 1)".

34
00:03:24,823 --> 00:03:26,536
Hey, Conan-kun?

35
00:03:29,875 --> 00:03:31,754
Conan-kun, hello?
Ah...

36
00:03:32,296 --> 00:03:33,508
Huh? What?

37
00:03:33,591 --> 00:03:37,306
What do you mean "what"?
You keep looking around.

38
00:03:37,390 --> 00:03:38,893
Is there someone
suspicious here?

39
00:03:38,977 --> 00:03:43,151
Oh... no, don't worry about it.
It's nothing like that.

40
00:03:43,235 --> 00:03:44,655
Really?

41
00:03:45,657 --> 00:03:47,326
This is bad.

42
00:03:47,410 --> 00:03:50,417
Ever since then, I keep feeling
like someone's watching me.

43
00:03:51,586 --> 00:03:53,046
I told Jodie...

44
00:03:53,130 --> 00:03:55,635
that couple might've been
the ones in black...

45
00:03:55,719 --> 00:03:57,764
just in case, but...

46
00:03:59,183 --> 00:04:03,066
If they've caught on
to that one thing...

47
00:04:03,943 --> 00:04:07,366
Calm down. It's fine.
It's still fine.

48
00:04:10,039 --> 00:04:13,713
Oh... are you feeling sick,
Conan-kun?

49
00:04:13,796 --> 00:04:14,923
You're drenched in sweat.

50
00:04:15,007 --> 00:04:16,636
Huh? What?

51
00:04:17,219 --> 00:04:21,687
We were going to have lunch
with my mom in Chinatown later...

52
00:04:21,771 --> 00:04:23,106
Should we cancel and go home?

53
00:04:23,190 --> 00:04:26,697
Ah... I'm fine.
I was just thinking about something.

54
00:04:27,949 --> 00:04:29,035
Is that so?

55
00:04:29,285 --> 00:04:32,626
I got assigned some
tough homework, that's all.

56
00:04:33,503 --> 00:04:34,838
(camera shutter)

57
00:04:36,425 --> 00:04:38,053
A shutter sound?

58
00:04:44,190 --> 00:04:46,277
I'm not imagining it.

59
00:04:46,361 --> 00:04:49,325
Someone really is
watching me.

60
00:04:49,409 --> 00:04:52,039
But who... and why?

61
00:04:52,123 --> 00:04:53,543
(camera shutter)

62
00:04:53,626 --> 00:04:56,381
Again.
Closer than last time.

63
00:04:56,465 --> 00:04:59,220
Where? Where are they
shooting from?

64
00:04:59,555 --> 00:05:00,557
(camera shutter)

65
00:05:01,434 --> 00:05:02,978
Hey, you two.

66
00:05:03,061 --> 00:05:05,232
What are you doing
in a place like this?

67
00:05:06,401 --> 00:05:08,906
Sera-san, what about you?

68
00:05:09,323 --> 00:05:11,202
I'm working.

69
00:05:11,286 --> 00:05:15,462
You know a girl in Class A
named Keiko Kitao?

70
00:05:15,545 --> 00:05:17,214
Oh, Kei-chan?

71
00:05:17,549 --> 00:05:21,640
Through her, her older sister
hired me for a job.

72
00:05:21,724 --> 00:05:22,809
See...

73
00:05:23,561 --> 00:05:25,314
Sitting in that chair over there...

74
00:05:26,065 --> 00:05:29,071
That's Rumi Kitao,
a third-year university student.

75
00:05:29,155 --> 00:05:32,161
And the man sitting next to her...

76
00:05:32,244 --> 00:05:35,250
is Kenya Settsu,
a fourth-year student.

77
00:05:36,127 --> 00:05:39,593
Those two have been dating
for the past six months.

78
00:05:39,676 --> 00:05:43,726
She wants to introduce him
to her parents as a marriage prospect...

79
00:05:43,810 --> 00:05:46,022
but rumor has it
he's a playboy...

80
00:05:46,105 --> 00:05:49,863
and she suspects he hasn't fully
cut things off with his ex.

81
00:05:49,947 --> 00:05:50,949
Huh.

82
00:05:52,409 --> 00:05:54,163
So I've been investigating that.

83
00:05:54,247 --> 00:05:55,249
I see.

84
00:05:55,667 --> 00:05:57,754
So it's an affair
investigation.

85
00:05:58,213 --> 00:05:59,591
So, how's it looking?

86
00:05:59,675 --> 00:06:02,806
Hm? Right now, it's gray.

87
00:06:02,889 --> 00:06:07,314
He still hasn't returned the spare key
to his ex's apartment...

88
00:06:07,398 --> 00:06:10,530
and this place happens to be
that ex's building.

89
00:06:10,905 --> 00:06:14,454
But is it okay to be telling
us all this?

90
00:06:14,746 --> 00:06:18,211
It's fine. You two can keep
a secret, right?

91
00:06:18,504 --> 00:06:19,965
Ah, haha...

92
00:06:20,048 --> 00:06:22,888
So, what are you two
doing here?

93
00:06:23,514 --> 00:06:25,267
This is Kanagawa Prefecture,
you know.

94
00:06:25,350 --> 00:06:28,148
My mom took on a job
from a resident here...

95
00:06:28,231 --> 00:06:30,360
and she's in a meeting
right now.

96
00:06:30,445 --> 00:06:33,116
We were supposed to have lunch
once it wrapped up, but...

97
00:06:33,199 --> 00:06:35,120
(phone ringing)

98
00:06:35,203 --> 00:06:37,667
Oh, it's from my mom.

99
00:06:38,878 --> 00:06:42,092
What? No way.
You can't get away?

100
00:06:42,176 --> 00:06:44,806
But I'm starving.

101
00:06:44,890 --> 00:06:48,313
Sorry, sweetie. The meeting's running long.

102
00:06:48,564 --> 00:06:52,279
If you're hungry, go ahead and grab
a quick bite with Conan-kun first.

103
00:06:52,363 --> 00:06:54,785
Let's meet back in this lobby
in the evening.

104
00:06:54,868 --> 00:06:56,412
Okaay.

105
00:06:57,414 --> 00:07:00,421
Guess I'll just buy
a rice ball at the convenience store.

106
00:07:00,505 --> 00:07:02,926
Then why not have those two
treat you to lunch?

107
00:07:03,009 --> 00:07:04,011
Huh?

108
00:07:04,095 --> 00:07:05,890
They've got plans
to have lunch today...

109
00:07:05,974 --> 00:07:08,353
with the ex joining them.

110
00:07:08,729 --> 00:07:11,902
Quit joking.
We've never even met them.

111
00:07:12,487 --> 00:07:14,073
It's an undercover operation.

112
00:07:14,156 --> 00:07:16,537
Huh... undercover?

113
00:07:16,620 --> 00:07:19,584
For Keiko-kun's sake,
in Class A.

114
00:07:19,668 --> 00:07:21,254
Huh? You're kidding?

115
00:07:21,714 --> 00:07:24,803
Wasn't your little sister
supposed to come later?

116
00:07:24,886 --> 00:07:26,598
It's a pretty famous place...

117
00:07:26,682 --> 00:07:30,815
and it was a real pain
to get a reservation for her too.

118
00:07:31,024 --> 00:07:32,736
It can't be helped.

119
00:07:32,819 --> 00:07:35,533
She said something
suddenly came up with a friend.

120
00:07:35,616 --> 00:07:39,541
What? Don't tell me
you're after my little sister.

121
00:07:39,624 --> 00:07:43,716
Of course not. I just thought
she'd liven up the mood.

122
00:07:44,341 --> 00:07:48,476
Today's supposed to be a make-up dinner
between me and Wakka, right?

123
00:07:48,559 --> 00:07:51,607
I haven't really spoken to Wakka
since we broke up.

124
00:07:52,609 --> 00:07:55,656
Right. Well, Kaga's coming
later...

125
00:07:55,740 --> 00:07:57,242
so he'll get things lively.

126
00:07:57,326 --> 00:07:59,288
Oh, um...
Huh?

127
00:07:59,790 --> 00:08:02,837
Are you by any chance
Kei-chan Kitao's older sister?

128
00:08:02,921 --> 00:08:03,923
Eh... yes.

129
00:08:05,383 --> 00:08:10,185
I'm Ran Mouri. I was in the same class
as her last year.

130
00:08:10,268 --> 00:08:13,984
She showed me photos of you
a few times...

131
00:08:14,068 --> 00:08:16,030
so I thought it might be you.

132
00:08:16,114 --> 00:08:19,955
Oh, really?
Heh, what a coincidence.

133
00:08:21,249 --> 00:08:24,422
Actually, today I was supposed
to take Keiko-kun's place...

134
00:08:24,506 --> 00:08:27,344
and join the meal myself.

135
00:08:27,428 --> 00:08:30,142
If that guy's a playboy
like the rumors say...

136
00:08:30,225 --> 00:08:34,484
I figured he'd make eyes at me
behind her sister's back.

137
00:08:34,901 --> 00:08:38,534
But you've got a better figure
and you're cuter than me...

138
00:08:38,617 --> 00:08:40,454
so could you take this role?

139
00:08:40,538 --> 00:08:41,582
Huh?

140
00:08:41,832 --> 00:08:43,502
If he really is that kind of man...

141
00:08:43,586 --> 00:08:47,342
I'm sure he'll bite
if we dangle some bait.

142
00:08:47,677 --> 00:08:51,184
All right.
First, casually cast the bait...

143
00:08:55,943 --> 00:08:57,864
Um...
Hm?

144
00:08:59,951 --> 00:09:02,039
Co... Conan-kun.

145
00:09:02,122 --> 00:09:05,295
We're hungry, but we haven't
decided what to eat, right?

146
00:09:05,378 --> 00:09:06,965
Y... yeah.

147
00:09:07,049 --> 00:09:08,969
That wasn't casual at all.

148
00:09:09,053 --> 00:09:11,475
Then why not eat with us?

149
00:09:11,558 --> 00:09:12,602
Huh?

150
00:09:12,685 --> 00:09:15,775
One more kid won't make
much difference.

151
00:09:15,858 --> 00:09:18,989
Th... thank you so much.

152
00:09:19,073 --> 00:09:21,285
He took the bait
that easily.

153
00:09:21,954 --> 00:09:23,540
Perfect.

154
00:09:26,212 --> 00:09:27,339
Still...

155
00:09:27,757 --> 00:09:31,473
Wakka's late. It's already
past noon.

156
00:09:31,556 --> 00:09:33,101
Can't be helped.

157
00:09:33,477 --> 00:09:35,982
She was drinking until five this morning...
- Kaga Mitsuaki (22), university student.

158
00:09:36,065 --> 00:09:38,111
so she's probably
still out cold.

159
00:09:38,194 --> 00:09:40,533
Oh, you're here, Kaga.

160
00:09:40,783 --> 00:09:43,246
This lobby has a restroom,
doesn't it?

161
00:09:43,329 --> 00:09:45,459
Yeah, past the elevator.

162
00:09:46,420 --> 00:09:48,882
Then I'll go take care
of business real quick.

163
00:09:48,966 --> 00:09:51,888
In that case, I'll go check on Wakka.

164
00:09:51,972 --> 00:09:54,519
Oh, if you're going
to Wakka's room...

165
00:09:55,980 --> 00:09:58,109
return this spare key
for me.

166
00:09:58,192 --> 00:09:59,236
Huh?

167
00:09:59,738 --> 00:10:02,367
I don't need it anymore.

168
00:10:02,452 --> 00:10:03,704
Kenya...

169
00:10:05,165 --> 00:10:07,044
Ah... oh...

170
00:10:07,294 --> 00:10:09,340
Hey now, don't drop it.

171
00:10:09,424 --> 00:10:10,760
Sorry.

172
00:10:11,762 --> 00:10:14,350
And now she's alone
with Ran-kun.

173
00:10:14,434 --> 00:10:17,482
If he's going to show his tail,
it'll be now.

174
00:10:17,690 --> 00:10:21,531
Ah... sorry, but could you
go along with her too?

175
00:10:21,615 --> 00:10:23,117
Huh?
Huh?

176
00:10:23,494 --> 00:10:26,248
If Wakka still hasn't
sobered up...

177
00:10:26,332 --> 00:10:28,629
she might lash out at her.

178
00:10:29,254 --> 00:10:30,800
That's true.

179
00:10:31,718 --> 00:10:35,601
I did steal Wakka's
boyfriend, after all...

180
00:10:35,893 --> 00:10:39,818
so with an unfamiliar girl along,
Wakka might stay calmer.

181
00:10:40,068 --> 00:10:42,573
I don't mind, but...

182
00:10:42,865 --> 00:10:44,159
Then please come along.

183
00:10:44,243 --> 00:10:45,579
Oh, okay.

184
00:10:46,122 --> 00:10:47,417
(sighs)

185
00:10:49,671 --> 00:10:53,679
Maybe she just suddenly
didn't want to see my face...

186
00:10:53,762 --> 00:10:56,016
and she's holed up in there.

187
00:10:56,100 --> 00:10:59,816
If so, tell her I want to meet
in person and apologize...

188
00:10:59,899 --> 00:11:01,903
for everything.
Okay.

189
00:11:03,072 --> 00:11:04,074
Hmm.

190
00:11:04,241 --> 00:11:05,326
Surprisingly...

191
00:11:05,578 --> 00:11:08,124
this guy's
pretty decent.

192
00:11:09,334 --> 00:11:12,717
(doorbell chiming)

193
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:14,344
No answer.

194
00:11:14,429 --> 00:11:16,265
(doorbell chiming)

195
00:11:16,348 --> 00:11:18,604
Maybe she really
is asleep.

196
00:11:19,564 --> 00:11:22,528
Then I guess I'll use this.

197
00:11:23,447 --> 00:11:24,949
Wakka?

198
00:11:25,868 --> 00:11:28,499
Are you sleeping?
(phone ringing)

199
00:11:28,582 --> 00:11:31,003
Oh.
(phone ringing)

200
00:11:31,086 --> 00:11:32,924
Sorry, it's a call.

201
00:11:33,007 --> 00:11:35,763
Sorry, but could you go
wake Wakka up?

202
00:11:35,846 --> 00:11:37,140
Huh?

203
00:11:43,361 --> 00:11:47,285
When Wakka comes home drunk,
she has a habit of sleeping in weird spots...

204
00:11:47,620 --> 00:11:50,124
so check inside the closet too.

205
00:11:50,208 --> 00:11:51,461
Oh, okay.

206
00:11:52,922 --> 00:11:56,178
Sorry to keep you waiting.
Huh? Hard to hear me?

207
00:11:56,513 --> 00:11:58,976
Then I'll step out
onto the balcony.

208
00:12:00,646 --> 00:12:03,234
Wakka-san,
are you here?

209
00:12:04,696 --> 00:12:05,739
Wakka-san?

210
00:12:06,825 --> 00:12:07,994
Wakka-san.

211
00:12:08,954 --> 00:12:13,045
This is troubling.
She's nowhere... oh.

212
00:12:16,636 --> 00:12:18,389
(shower running)
Oh.

213
00:12:18,473 --> 00:12:19,517
The bath?

214
00:12:20,184 --> 00:12:23,984
Um, I'm a friend
of Rumi-san's little sister...

215
00:12:24,067 --> 00:12:26,823
I was asked to come
get you, Wakka-san...

216
00:12:28,994 --> 00:12:31,248
Wa... Wakka-san?

217
00:12:33,712 --> 00:12:34,839
Are you okay?

218
00:12:35,131 --> 00:12:37,928
Wakka-san!

219
00:12:39,599 --> 00:12:43,356
Please hold on, Wakka-san.
Wakka-san.

220
00:12:43,440 --> 00:12:45,861
Wakka-sa... ngh.

221
00:13:00,407 --> 00:13:01,409
Ran-neechan.

222
00:13:02,161 --> 00:13:04,875
Ran-neechan, wake up.

223
00:13:06,169 --> 00:13:08,465
Ran-neechan! Ran-neechan!

224
00:13:08,549 --> 00:13:10,887
Ngh... Co... Conan-kun.

225
00:13:11,137 --> 00:13:13,141
Thank goodness.
You came to.

226
00:13:13,225 --> 00:13:16,314
You okay?
Sorry about all this.

227
00:13:16,397 --> 00:13:17,776
Sera-san.

228
00:13:18,151 --> 00:13:20,573
What... what happened to me?

229
00:13:20,657 --> 00:13:22,409
Ow, ow...

230
00:13:22,493 --> 00:13:24,455
You collapsed
in the bathroom.

231
00:13:24,915 --> 00:13:27,086
Oh no... it's terrible.

232
00:13:27,169 --> 00:13:30,092
Wakka-san was collapsed
in the bathroom, bleeding...

233
00:13:30,175 --> 00:13:32,471
Yeah, that's why... see.

234
00:13:33,139 --> 00:13:34,893
Oh... oh...

235
00:13:35,185 --> 00:13:38,316
The police are here
investigating now.

236
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:39,653
What happened?

237
00:13:40,279 --> 00:13:43,368
I heard the shower running
in this bathroom...

238
00:13:43,451 --> 00:13:47,459
and when I went in, Wakka-san
was collapsed in the steam...

239
00:13:47,544 --> 00:13:51,509
I tried to wake her,
but I suddenly blacked out...

240
00:13:51,719 --> 00:13:53,639
Did you see anyone
suspicious?

241
00:13:53,723 --> 00:13:54,808
No.

242
00:13:55,142 --> 00:13:58,566
I searched the closet too,
but there was no one...

243
00:13:58,649 --> 00:14:00,945
Huh?
Why the closet?

244
00:14:01,029 --> 00:14:05,078
Wakka-san has a habit of sleeping
in odd places when she comes home drunk...

245
00:14:05,162 --> 00:14:07,584
Rumi-san, who came to get her
with me...

246
00:14:07,667 --> 00:14:10,882
Oh, that's right.
Where's Rumi-san?

247
00:14:10,965 --> 00:14:12,552
I'm fine.

248
00:14:13,554 --> 00:14:16,059
I'm sorry for dragging you
into this mess.

249
00:14:16,142 --> 00:14:17,144
Rumi-san.

250
00:14:17,771 --> 00:14:18,898
Unfortunately...

251
00:14:18,981 --> 00:14:22,404
after I found you and Wakka
collapsed in the bathroom...

252
00:14:22,488 --> 00:14:26,789
I passed out too...
so I didn't see the culprit either.

253
00:14:27,081 --> 00:14:30,003
Since we didn't
come back for so long...

254
00:14:30,087 --> 00:14:32,007
Kenya and the others
came up, right?

255
00:14:32,091 --> 00:14:33,093
Yeah.

256
00:14:33,719 --> 00:14:36,391
Even after 30 minutes
you didn't come down...

257
00:14:36,474 --> 00:14:39,313
and you didn't answer
your phones either.

258
00:14:39,397 --> 00:14:42,069
So we explained the situation
to the building's management office...

259
00:14:42,152 --> 00:14:43,906
and had them unlock the door.

260
00:14:43,990 --> 00:14:45,367
Right?
Yeah.

261
00:14:45,785 --> 00:14:49,543
And then we found the three of you
piled up, collapsed in the bathroom...

262
00:14:49,626 --> 00:14:51,714
so we hurried
and called the police.

263
00:14:51,797 --> 00:14:52,799
Ngh...

264
00:14:52,882 --> 00:14:55,429
But what was that smell?

265
00:14:55,512 --> 00:14:57,600
I got woozy in the bathroom.

266
00:14:57,892 --> 00:14:59,730
It was chloroform.

267
00:15:03,445 --> 00:15:06,367
Hmph... it's a type
of anesthetic...

268
00:15:06,451 --> 00:15:09,081
Inhale a large amount
and you lose consciousness...

269
00:15:09,165 --> 00:15:11,837
and in some cases,
it can even kill you.

270
00:15:11,920 --> 00:15:15,510
It vaporized and filled
this entire bathroom.

271
00:15:15,595 --> 00:15:16,597
Huh?

272
00:15:16,889 --> 00:15:20,772
Well, seems this kid
turned on the ventilation fan right away...

273
00:15:21,439 --> 00:15:23,944
so you're all fine now.

274
00:15:24,236 --> 00:15:26,700
So Wakka was killed
with that anesthetic...

275
00:15:26,784 --> 00:15:29,623
Hey now, can't you tell
just by looking?

276
00:15:30,499 --> 00:15:32,545
She was beaten to death.

277
00:15:32,629 --> 00:15:36,385
Someone struck her head
with a blunt object and killed her.

278
00:15:37,513 --> 00:15:40,603
But if that's the case,
why use anesthetic...?

279
00:15:40,686 --> 00:15:43,526
And is the dead person
really Wakka?

280
00:15:43,609 --> 00:15:45,905
Her face is hidden
by that mask.

281
00:15:46,239 --> 00:15:48,994
Then let's have you
confirm it.

282
00:15:49,328 --> 00:15:50,372
Ah...

283
00:15:53,128 --> 00:15:55,006
Ah.
Ah, Wakka!

284
00:15:55,090 --> 00:15:58,597
Whoa now,
don't come in.

285
00:15:59,265 --> 00:16:03,022
But what a strange corpse.
She's winking.

286
00:16:03,314 --> 00:16:07,615
And... something's
dripping from the corner of her eye.

287
00:16:09,493 --> 00:16:10,997
Mascara?

288
00:16:13,878 --> 00:16:16,633
At a glance, it looks like
someone struck Wakka-san...

289
00:16:16,717 --> 00:16:19,973
from behind as she was about
to take a bath...

290
00:16:20,933 --> 00:16:22,854
but this might just be...

291
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:28,448
So, to sum it up...

292
00:16:28,908 --> 00:16:33,291
Today, you four had plans
to eat lunch together...

293
00:16:33,374 --> 00:16:35,086
and you were going to gather
in the early afternoon...

294
00:16:35,170 --> 00:16:38,384
in the lobby of the victim's
apartment building, here.

295
00:16:38,844 --> 00:16:42,977
But worried that she
wasn't coming down at all...

296
00:16:43,061 --> 00:16:46,067
Rumi-san and Ran-san,
who happened to be there...

297
00:16:46,150 --> 00:16:48,822
came up to this room
to check on her...

298
00:16:49,156 --> 00:16:51,327
but there was no answer
to the doorbell.

299
00:16:51,410 --> 00:16:53,624
So, with the key entrusted
to you by Settsu-san...

300
00:16:53,707 --> 00:16:56,212
who used to date the victim...

301
00:16:56,295 --> 00:16:59,385
you opened the front door
and went inside.

302
00:17:00,387 --> 00:17:04,646
Then, at that moment, a call came
from Settsu-san to Rumi-san...

303
00:17:04,729 --> 00:17:07,986
so Ran-san ended up
searching for her alone...

304
00:17:08,069 --> 00:17:11,033
and found her collapsed
in the bathroom...

305
00:17:11,117 --> 00:17:13,329
but passed out
from the chloroform...

306
00:17:13,413 --> 00:17:16,878
and Rumi-san, who came afterward,
also fell asleep.

307
00:17:17,254 --> 00:17:18,882
Then, 30 minutes later...

308
00:17:18,966 --> 00:17:21,137
worried about the two of you
who wouldn't return...

309
00:17:21,220 --> 00:17:23,308
you all rushed here...

310
00:17:23,391 --> 00:17:26,857
and found the three of them
collapsed in the bathroom.

311
00:17:27,190 --> 00:17:29,904
Yeah, that's pretty much it.

312
00:17:30,488 --> 00:17:33,328
The front door's deadbolt
was locked...

313
00:17:33,411 --> 00:17:37,419
so it took time to open it,
which delayed our call to the police.

314
00:17:37,502 --> 00:17:39,799
I... I'm the worrying type...

315
00:17:39,883 --> 00:17:43,139
I have a habit of locking up
right away wherever I go.

316
00:17:43,222 --> 00:17:46,520
Hmm... by the way, is it true
the victim was drinking...

317
00:17:46,605 --> 00:17:48,901
until five this morning?

318
00:17:48,984 --> 00:17:52,032
Yeah. Just the two of us,
in this room.

319
00:17:52,115 --> 00:17:56,165
I invited Settsu and Rumi too, but they said
they'd see her tomorrow anyway.

320
00:17:56,666 --> 00:18:00,549
I got an earful of complaints
about her ex, Settsu...

321
00:18:00,633 --> 00:18:02,553
right up until she
drank herself to sleep.

322
00:18:03,012 --> 00:18:05,308
So what about the front
door key?

323
00:18:05,392 --> 00:18:06,895
O... of course...

324
00:18:06,978 --> 00:18:10,694
When I left, I managed to wake Wakka
and had her lock it properly.

325
00:18:10,778 --> 00:18:11,947
Hmm...

326
00:18:13,784 --> 00:18:17,499
Still, this is some apartment
for one person to live in.

327
00:18:17,583 --> 00:18:20,965
Wakka's father is an executive
at a famous company.

328
00:18:21,257 --> 00:18:24,722
Well, the only one who wasn't
surprised by this place...

329
00:18:24,806 --> 00:18:28,605
was a first-year girl who joined
our club this year.

330
00:18:28,689 --> 00:18:33,406
Her parents... the chairman of an affiliated
group of that company, apparently.

331
00:18:33,489 --> 00:18:35,536
Hey.
Hm? Oh.

332
00:18:35,619 --> 00:18:39,334
When you and Ran-neechan
entered here with the spare key...

333
00:18:39,418 --> 00:18:42,090
it seems there was a call
from Settsu-san...

334
00:18:42,174 --> 00:18:43,760
What was it about?

335
00:18:43,844 --> 00:18:45,890
He asked me to look
for something.

336
00:18:46,223 --> 00:18:50,356
Back when he was dating Wakka,
he left something here...

337
00:18:50,440 --> 00:18:53,321
and he wanted me to find it
and bring it to him.

338
00:18:53,404 --> 00:18:55,784
Well, he'd asked me before...

339
00:18:55,868 --> 00:18:58,122
so I was going to do it
even without the call.

340
00:18:58,957 --> 00:19:01,086
What did he leave behind?

341
00:19:01,170 --> 00:19:04,009
A wristwatch.
One he was fond of.

342
00:19:04,761 --> 00:19:08,644
He figured it was probably
still left in the living room.

343
00:19:08,852 --> 00:19:11,190
If Wakka was still asleep...

344
00:19:11,273 --> 00:19:13,779
he wanted me to slip in
with the spare key...

345
00:19:13,862 --> 00:19:15,699
and quietly retrieve it...

346
00:19:16,283 --> 00:19:18,412
but it seems
I couldn't find it.

347
00:19:18,496 --> 00:19:21,126
Maybe Wakka found it
and threw it away.

348
00:19:21,210 --> 00:19:22,588
The living room...

349
00:19:22,672 --> 00:19:25,761
that's the big room
with the balcony, right?

350
00:19:25,844 --> 00:19:26,972
Yes.

351
00:19:27,640 --> 00:19:30,186
A call came in and I stepped out
onto the balcony...

352
00:19:30,270 --> 00:19:32,567
so it was good timing
to search, but...

353
00:19:32,650 --> 00:19:34,904
This is a high-rise
apartment...

354
00:19:34,988 --> 00:19:37,910
so the signal's weak unless
you go out on the balcony.

355
00:19:37,994 --> 00:19:41,208
That's why you asked her
to look for Wakka, right?

356
00:19:41,292 --> 00:19:42,712
Oh, yes.

357
00:19:42,795 --> 00:19:44,841
Which means...

358
00:19:46,010 --> 00:19:49,892
Rumi-san came in the front door
and went into the living room on the left...

359
00:19:49,976 --> 00:19:53,482
while Ran searched the right side,
where the bedroom is.

360
00:19:54,026 --> 00:19:58,075
Speaking of the balcony...
when Wakka came home drunk...

361
00:19:58,159 --> 00:20:00,288
she slept on the balcony
sometimes too, right?

362
00:20:00,371 --> 00:20:03,252
Yeah, I heard that story before.

363
00:20:04,296 --> 00:20:06,508
She called me pretty drunk...

364
00:20:06,593 --> 00:20:09,724
saying she was sobering up
in the breeze...

365
00:20:09,807 --> 00:20:11,770
but she fell asleep
mid-call.

366
00:20:12,605 --> 00:20:14,191
I came over worried...

367
00:20:14,274 --> 00:20:17,113
and she was leaning against the balcony,
sound asleep.

368
00:20:17,197 --> 00:20:19,493
She slept under the bed
once too.

369
00:20:19,577 --> 00:20:21,455
But this time...

370
00:20:21,706 --> 00:20:26,298
it wasn't the balcony or under the bed,
but the bathroom where she slept.

371
00:20:26,382 --> 00:20:27,760
As a corpse.

372
00:20:30,056 --> 00:20:33,104
And the one who put her
through that...

373
00:20:33,187 --> 00:20:35,483
is one of the two of you...

374
00:20:35,859 --> 00:20:39,157
who had the key
to this room.

375
00:20:39,241 --> 00:20:41,328
H... hey...
Hold on a second.

376
00:20:41,788 --> 00:20:45,963
Settsu, the ex, had the spare key,
but I don't have any key...

377
00:20:46,046 --> 00:20:48,969
You drank until this morning
and got the victim drunk...

378
00:20:49,052 --> 00:20:51,975
then secretly took the key home,
didn't you?

379
00:20:52,058 --> 00:20:53,436
When you rushed here...

380
00:20:53,519 --> 00:20:56,275
you could just leave it lying around
and cover it up.

381
00:20:56,358 --> 00:20:58,070
Ah...
Maybe...

382
00:20:58,154 --> 00:21:01,118
you were even here right up until
the gathering time in the afternoon...

383
00:21:01,201 --> 00:21:03,456
A... and Rumi might have
a key too.

384
00:21:03,540 --> 00:21:04,542
Hm?

385
00:21:04,625 --> 00:21:08,800
She used to share this place with Wakka
before Settsu and Wakka started dating.

386
00:21:08,884 --> 00:21:11,180
I returned my key
ages ago.

387
00:21:11,263 --> 00:21:12,933
I see...

388
00:21:16,148 --> 00:21:20,532
If all three of you
could have had a key...

389
00:21:20,616 --> 00:21:23,830
then all three of you
could have committed the crime.

390
00:21:23,914 --> 00:21:25,709
No.
Ah...

391
00:21:26,961 --> 00:21:30,510
The only ones who could have killed Wakka-san
before Ran-kun found her...

392
00:21:31,930 --> 00:21:34,852
are Settsu-san and Kaga-san,
the two of them.

393
00:21:34,936 --> 00:21:36,606
Ah...
What?

394
00:21:38,150 --> 00:21:40,823
Kaga-san arrived just before...

395
00:21:40,906 --> 00:21:44,539
Ran-kun and Rumi-san went up
to call on Wakka-san's room...

396
00:21:45,081 --> 00:21:49,882
and about 30 minutes before that,
Settsu-san stepped away to the restroom, right?

397
00:21:50,508 --> 00:21:54,182
If those two had the key
to Wakka-san's room...

398
00:21:55,059 --> 00:21:58,357
they could have used the stairs,
which have no security camera...

399
00:21:58,440 --> 00:22:02,323
and killed Wakka-san
without anyone seeing.

400
00:22:03,284 --> 00:22:05,288
On that point, Rumi-san...

401
00:22:05,371 --> 00:22:08,085
was with me the whole time until we got here.
Ah.

402
00:22:09,087 --> 00:22:12,595
She didn't even go to the restroom
until we went to Wakka-san's room...

403
00:22:13,429 --> 00:22:14,849
so she couldn't have done it.

404
00:22:14,932 --> 00:22:16,644
You were with Rumi?

405
00:22:16,728 --> 00:22:19,734
Wait, who the heck are you?
A detective.

406
00:22:19,817 --> 00:22:21,403
Huh?
Huh?

407
00:22:23,533 --> 00:22:25,662
Rumi-san hired me.

408
00:22:32,175 --> 00:22:38,187
♪~

409
00:23:46,532 --> 00:23:51,793
~♪

410
00:23:52,251 --> 00:23:53,755
In any case...

411
00:23:54,882 --> 00:23:56,803
Ngh...
Ah.

412
00:23:58,305 --> 00:24:00,142
Ah... sorry.

413
00:24:00,560 --> 00:24:02,564
Thanks for picking it up.

414
00:24:02,898 --> 00:24:04,109
Here.

415
00:24:04,192 --> 00:24:05,946
Don't drop it again.

416
00:24:06,029 --> 00:24:07,031
Hm...

417
00:24:07,198 --> 00:24:11,331
If that corpse
wasn't Wakka-san...

418
00:24:11,414 --> 00:24:12,751
then that changes things.

419
00:24:12,835 --> 00:24:13,837
Huh?

420
00:24:14,254 --> 00:24:15,841
Ah...
Wh... what did you say?

421
00:24:15,861 --> 00:24:17,361
Next Conan,

422
00:24:17,361 --> 00:24:21,261
"The Restroom Where Ran Also Collapsed (Part 2)".

423
00:24:36,861 --> 00:24:38,761
Next Conan's Hint:

424
00:24:38,761 --> 00:24:41,461
"Wink".

425
00:24:41,461 --> 00:24:43,361
It's almost June. From May to June.
426
00:24:43,361 --> 00:24:45,261
Mascara from the eyes.
